# Josh-Bear BBP port — real-boot serial proof
# Core commit: ae5d3e2 (v1.1). QEMU x86_64 + Limine + virtio-net.
# The Josh kernel ('lisabeth') runs bbp_josh_init() right after heap_init; the
# adapter synthesizes HHDM+MEMORY_MAP+FRAMEBUFFER+SMP+SECURITY from Limine + a
# boot-entropy gather, and the frozen BBP parser validates the CRC-sealed list.
# Josh then VERIFIES the SECURITY entropy blob (bbp_verify_blob) and seeds its
# CSPRNG from it — BBP in the read path, not just synthesis. (0x5 = 5 tags hex.)

